<item>
            <title>[MATH-1439] IntervalsSet getBoundarySize() method fails when interval is a single point</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-1439</link>
                <project id="12310485" key="MATH">Commons Math</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After creating an IntervalsSet representing a single point, calls to getBoundarySize() fail with a MathInternalError. The exception is thrown from the o.a.c.m.geometry.partitioning.Characterization class, which does not expect the BSP tree nodes it visits to have hyperplanes that are similar to those of their parents. However, IntervalsSet can (and should be allowed to) create such a tree. I believe that the Characterization class should be updated to handle this situation gracefully.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here is an example of the failing code:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;IntervalsSet set = new IntervalsSet(1.0, 1.0, 1e-10);&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;set.getBoundarySize();&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Pull request: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/commons-math/pull/74&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/commons-math/pull/74&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
